defs.name: supports_credentials
defs.docs: Allows users to make authenticated requests

attributes.value: / Allows users to make authenticated requests
/ If true, injects the `Access-Control-Allow-Credentials` header in
/ responses. This allows cookies and credentials to be submitted
/ This option cannot be used in conjunction with an `allowed_origin` set
/ Builder panics if credentials are allowed, but the Origin is set to "*".
/ This is not allowed by W3C

defs.name: disable_vary_header
defs.docs: Disable `Vary` header support.

attributes.value: / When enabled the header `Vary: Origin` will be returned as per the W3
/ Setting this header when the `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` is
/ dynamically generated (e.g. when there is more than one allowed
/ origin, and an Origin than '*' is returned) informs CDNs and other
/ caches that the CORS headers are dynamic, and cannot be cached.
/ By default `vary` header support is enabled.
